Sentencas: Proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell (H-SOFC) is an emerging energy conversion device, with lower activation energy and higher energy utilization efficiency.
Titulo: Barium-doped Pr2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+δ with triple conducting characteristics as cathode for intermediate temperature proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: However, the deficiency of highly active cathode materials still remains a major challenge for the development of H-SOFC.
Titulo: Barium-doped Pr2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+δ with triple conducting characteristics as cathode for intermediate temperature proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Therefore, in this work, K2NiF4-type cathode materials Pr2-xBaxNi0.6Cu0.4O4+delta (x = 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3), single-phase tripleconducting (e /O-2 /H+) oxides, are prepared for intermediate temperature H-SOFCs and exhibit good oxygen reduction reaction activity.
Titulo: Barium-doped Pr2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+δ with triple conducting characteristics as cathode for intermediate temperature proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The investigation demonstrates that doping Ba into Pr2-xBaxNi0.6Cu0.4O4+delta can increase its electrochemical performance through enhancing electrical conductivity, oxygen vacancy concentration and proton conductivity.
Titulo: Barium-doped Pr2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+δ with triple conducting characteristics as cathode for intermediate temperature proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: EIS tests are carried at 750 degrees C and the minimum polarization impedances are obtained when x = 0.2, which are 0.068 Omega.cm(2) in air and 1.336 Omega.cm(2) in wet argon, respectively.
Titulo: Barium-doped Pr2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+δ with triple conducting characteristics as cathode for intermediate temperature proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The peak power density of the cell with Pr1.8Ba0.2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+delta cathode is 298 mW.cm(-2) at 750 degrees C in air with humidified hydrogen as fuel.
Titulo: Barium-doped Pr2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+δ with triple conducting characteristics as cathode for intermediate temperature proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Based on the above results, Ba-doped Pr2-xBaxNi0.6Cu0.4O4+delta can be a good candidate material for SOFC cathode applications.
Titulo: Barium-doped Pr2Ni0.6Cu0.4O4+δ with triple conducting characteristics as cathode for intermediate temperature proton conducting solid oxide fuel cell
